  "response_text": "A bright tabletop display opens with a yellow Old El Paso “Hard ’n Soft Taco Kit” box standing upright in the center. The box shows a taco and soft tortilla, with tomatoes and a cut lime arranged to the left and a small dish of green garnish to the right. The background is softly blurred, suggesting people moving in a warm, casual eating setting. The website “oldelpaso.com.au” appears near the bottom.\n\nThe imagery then shifts abruptly to a pale, sunlit seaside cliff. A small human figure stands high on jagged rocks against a washed-out sky. Nearby, several young women in swimwear gather among rocks; one dark-haired woman in a red bikini holds an old-fashioned handheld movie camera up to her eye, filming. A blonde woman in a light bikini smiles broadly and raises one hand to shade her eyes, then lifts her other arm as if waving or cheering. Another woman in a green one-piece swimsuit smiles beside her. High above, a man in dark swim briefs stands at the cliff edge and waves. He then leaps outward from the rock face, his body stretched away from the cliff, and moments later the view opens to a narrow rocky inlet below, where white spray bursts up near the water between steep stone walls.\n\nIn a dense jungle, an older white man with swept-back gray hair and a full gray beard moves through shadowy green foliage. He wears a light-colored jacket over an open-collared shirt, with a strap crossing his chest, giving him the look of an explorer. Behind him are men with red face paint around their eyes, bare chests, necklaces, and large circular ear ornaments. The older man pauses and looks ahead with a calm, alert expression while the men behind him watch closely. Light filters through bamboo and leaves, creating a humid, mottled atmosphere. As he continues through the plants, a reddish wash of light briefly fills the scene, then he appears backlit by a bright opening in the jungle, half-hidden by large leaves. He parts the foliage and advances, still composed. A closer view shows his lined face turning to the side. One of the face-painted men is then seen in profile, smiling, with red paint across his eyes and a pale horizontal ornament or stick near his mouth, surrounded by thick greenery.\n\nThe setting changes to a medical tent or field hospital. A dark-haired, bearded man lies shirtless on a bed with white pillows and sheets. Medical workers in khaki uniforms gather around him; one woman wears a stethoscope, and an IV bag and examination lamp hang nearby. The man looks down as hands work near his chest or shoulder, then he glances up and speaks or reacts with a relaxed, amused expression. The female doctor at his side smiles and laughs. A wider view shows several medical staff around the bed, all appearing cheerful rather than alarmed. One worker sits close to the man’s right side, attending to him, while others stand nearby, smiling. The man remains reclined and calm, participating with his hands near the area being treated.\n\nA misty hot spring follows. Several Japanese macaques, with thick gray-brown fur and pink faces, sit chest-deep in steaming water. Snowy rocks and foggy air fill the background. Three monkeys dominate the foreground: one faces left, one looks forward, and another tilts its pink face upward. Behind them, the older gray-bearded man slowly rises from the water among the monkeys, his head and shoulders emerging through the steam as if he belongs comfortably in the scene.\n\nThe final setting is a dark, elegant bar or lounge. The older gray-haired, gray-bearded man sits at a small table between two smiling women in evening attire, with another person partly visible at the far left. Tall glasses of golden beer with thick white foam stand on the table alongside green Dos Equis bottles. A red lamp glows in the background, and a red glass ashtray or candleholder sits near the center of the table. The man wears a dark jacket over a white shirt and looks directly forward, then toward the others, while the women smile at him. He lifts a green Dos Equis bottle with a red “XX” label, holding it upright as if making a quiet toast. Small legal text appears along the bottom, including “CERVEZAS MEXICANAS, WHITE PLAINS, NY.”\n\nA product-focused view places a green Dos Equis bottle in the center foreground on a coaster, its cream label and red double-X mark clearly visible. A tall glass of beer stands behind it, with the red glass object and a resting hand nearby on the glossy tabletop. Small text along the bottom says to enjoy Dos Equis responsibly. The commercial ends on a dark background with the Dos Equis logo on the left: “Cerveza XX Dos Equis,” followed by the slogan “Stay thirsty, my friends” and the website “Dosequis.com.” On the right, the older bearded man’s face is shown in a serious, steady portrait, looking slightly toward the viewer.",
